The President of the Republic of Niger, Mahamadou Issoufou, has been elected the new chairperson of the ECOWAS Authority of Heads of States and Government. This comes after a day-long closed door meeting held at the Presidential Villa in Abuja. Pretty Issoufou has been the leader of the Francophone Niger Republic since 2011 and takes over from the immediate past chairperson, President Muhammadu Buhari. BREAKING: Niger President emerges new ECOWAS Chairman Nigerien leader Issoufou arrives Abuja for signing of MOU on Refinery As Nigeria’s refineries fail: We’ll Export Petrol to Nigeria  - Nigerien President Issoufou Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin